           <!-- LHS -->
           <div class="col-md-7 col-lg-7">
	The flip angle (a.k.a. tip angle, nutation angle) refers to the angle between the net magnetization and $B_0$. The stronger the RF pulse applied or/and the longer duration of the pulse, the greater the flip angle. A wider angle means that the net $M$ experiences a larger rotation or is tipped to a larger degree relative to $B_0$ when the RF pulse is applied. The symbol for flip angle is $\alpha$ and its units are degrees or radians. ($\pi$ = $180^{\circ}$)
